  "text": "[r] 2 such that no matrix in F is an (i, j)-matrix, then K m (i, j) ∈ Avoid(m, r, F ), where K m is the simple (0, 1)-matrix of m rows and 2 m columns, thus forb(m, r, F ) ≥ 2 m . On the other hand, forb(m, r, Sym(F )) is of polynomial order of magnitude, consequently forb(m, r, S(F )) is polynomial, as well, as it was shown in [CITATION_1] .",
